                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Office of the Secretary<lb/>
                OF THE<lb/>
                German and Polish Synagogue&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>Montreal&#44; Aug. 23<hi rend="sup">rd</hi> 5646<lb/>
                1886<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev. S Morais<lb/></p>
            <p>Philadelphia P. A.<lb/></p>
            <p>Dear Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>We are about completing a New<lb/> Synagogue for&#44; the erection of which&#44; this Congregation<lb/> has strained every nerve&#44; the edifice itself&#44; though not a<lb/> <hi rend="underline">very</hi> expensive one&#44; will be the finest in Canada&#44; and one<lb/> of which the Orthodox Jews of this Country at least&#44;<lb/> may well be proud of&#44; this Board has resolved&#44; that since<lb/> the <sic>Allmighty</sic> spared and assisted us in erecting a<lb/> suitable place of worship&#44; we shall celebrate the occasion in<lb/> a suitable manner&#44; and in a way to show the world that<lb/> Orthodox Judaism is not dead.  We therefore&#44; beg to ask you<lb/> to come and deliver an oration&#44; in conjunction with Reverend<lb/> Mr Friedlander&#44; our Minister&#44; at the consecration&#44; on Sept. 15th&#44;<lb/> We are prompted to make this request of you from the knowledge&#44;<lb/> of the stand you have taken in Judaism&#44; and that your whole<lb/> life has been spent in defending our sacred religion.<lb/></p>
            <p>We therefore hope that you will not deny us the honor&#44; of<lb/> taking the lead in dedicating our new building to the<lb/> worship of God.  I may here add that in undertaking this<lb/> building we have spent more than our means would allow&#44;<lb/> and may not be in a position to remunerate you for your valuable<lb/> service&#44; as much as we would like to&#44; but we sincerely trust<lb/> that this will not prevent you from&#45;&#45;what must be a pleasure to you<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>Office of the Secretary<lb/>
                OF THE<lb/>
                German and Polish Synagogue&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>Montreal&#44; <hi rend="underline">2</hi> 564<lb/>
                188<lb/></p>
            <p>&#45;taking part in such a ceremony&#44; on receipt of your kind<lb/> acceptance we will forward you a check for your expenses&#44; &#38;c &#38;c&#44;<lb/> Hoping to be favoured with an early reply.<lb/>  I am your Obed&#39;t Servant<lb/> Harris Vineberg<lb/> Hon&#39;y Sec&#39;y<lb/></p>
            <p>address&#44; 752 Craig St							G &#38; P Cong<lb/></p>
            </body>
